Kubernetes Cluster Setup (v1.30) - Ubuntu 22.04
1. Pre-Flight (Both Nodes)

• Disable Swap: `sudo swapoff -a` `sudo sed -i '/ swap / s/^\(.*\)$/#\1/g' /etc/fstab`

• Kernel Modules: `cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf overlay br_netfilter EOF` `sudo modprobe overlay && sudo modprobe br_netfilter`

• Networking: `cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/k8s.conf net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables  = 1 net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables = 1 net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1 EOF` `sudo sysctl --system`

2. Container Runtime - Containerd (Both Nodes)

• `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y containerd`

• `sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd`

• `sudo containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml > /dev/null`

• `sudo sed -i 's/SystemdCgroup = false/SystemdCgroup = true/g' /etc/containerd/config.toml`

• `sudo systemctl restart containerd`

3. K8s Tools (Both Nodes)

• `sudo mkdir -p -m 755 /etc/apt/keyrings`

• `curl -fsSL [suspicious link removed] | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg`

• `echo 'deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] [suspicious link removed] /' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list`

• `sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl`

• `sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl`

4. Initialize Master (Master Only)

• `sudo kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16 --apiserver-advertise-address=<MASTER_PRIVATE_IP>`

• Setup Config: `mkdir -p $HOME/.kube` `sudo cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config` `sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config`

• Network Plugin: `kubectl apply -f https://github.com/flannel-io/flannel/releases/latest/download/kube-flannel.yml`

5. Join Worker (Worker Only)

• Run the `kubeadm join` command generated by the Master init.

6. Deployment Test (Master Only)

• `kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx --replicas=3`

• `kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80 --type=NodePort --name=nginx-service`

• `kubectl patch svc nginx-service -p '{"spec":{"ports":[{"port":80,"nodePort":30080}]}}'`

7. Cloud Firewall (AWS Console)

• Port 30080: Allow from 0.0.0.0/0

• Port 6443: Allow from Worker IP

• Port 8472 (UDP): Allow for Flannel between nodes

8. Access Nginx Service
• Access via `http://<MASTER_PUBLIC_IP>:30080`
9. Additional Notes
• Ensure security groups and network ACLs allow necessary traffic.
